desc: I’m a member of a Chinese Yoyo performance group known as the Pro-Yos!
We perform at several events each semester, culminating in a big showcase performance at the end of the spring semester.
I also served as the club’s secretary for one semester.
node.name: Cornell Pro-Yos

desc: I am part of Cornell’s Engineering Ambassadors, where I am responsible for giving tours for prospective and newly admitted students to the college of engineering as well as hosting Q&A sessions.
node.name: Engineering Ambassadors

desc: I am a general member of the Association of Computer Science Undergraduates (ACSU).
I’m mostly involved with the group’s mentorship program, where I provided guidance to underclassmen in the CS major and offered advice to those considering a CS major.
node.name: ACSU
